"exocrine glands male reproductive system, natural or artificial opening. this class includes one or more of 20 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the exocrine gland of the male reproductive system via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0v.. . "
"exocrine glands male reproductive system, natural or artificial opening. this class includes one or more of 20 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the exocrine gland of the male reproductive system via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0v.. resection of prostate,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to resection of prostate,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0vt08zz. "

"testicular structures-epididymis scrotum, percutaneous approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 20 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the testicular structures-epididymis and scrotum, with percutaneous approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0v.. destruction of scrotum,  percutaneous approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to destruction of scrotum,  percutaneous approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0v553zz. "

"testicular structures-epididymis scrotum, percutaneous endoscopic approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 20 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the testicular structures-epididymis and scrotum, with percutaneous endoscopic approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0v.. destruction of scrotum,  percutaneous endoscopic approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to destruction of scrotum,  percutaneous endoscopic approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0v554zz.
